commit.message:
Prevents error when name is an NaN

The _chrconvert() function barfs with an inscrutable error when passed a NaN float (and other non-string values). This cast prevents the failure, and allows use of those non-string sorts of things. This will only apply to 'name', 'description', 'text', 'linkname', 'linkdescription', 'message', 'change', 'create', 'delete', 'link' attributes passed in.
